Image quora.com
* It's not a question of how many reviews you have, it's a question of how good they are. Anyone can pump out reviews - what Amazon wants is reviews that help people buy more stuff. Are your reviews getting constantly upvoted? Are they CONSISTENTLY the review that's helpful to the potential buyer? Most important to Amazon - is yours the review that people click on right before they hit the buy button? Trust me - Amazon tracks this. If you're one of the reviewers that make people hit the buy button instantly, Amazon wants more of you. And more reviews from you. It comes down to quality reviews that make people want to buy something from Amazon. https://www.quora.com/How-many-reviews-do-you-have-to-write-to-be-accepted-into-the-Amazon-Vine-program
